          {
            "text": "A five-minute bedtime tapping practice from Day 30 of a 30-day sleep programme. The final night tap closes the programme by naming what the body has already become: breath that is slower, shoulders that carry less, nights that feel like home rather than something to get through. The reframe anchors calm as permanent, a change that carries forward into every night that follows.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
